## 7. KEY FEATURES & VALIDATION

### Static Headers Support
✓ Already fully implemented
- Form UI with dynamic add/remove rows
- Client-side validation (non-empty, no duplicates, no restricted names)
- Server-side validation before encryption
- AES-256-GCM encryption (via `TOOL_ENCRYPTION_KEY`)
- Decryption on-demand during tool discovery
- Header map building for HTTP requests
- Password-type input for header values in UI

### OAuth Support
✓ Already fully implemented
- Auto-discovery of OAuth metadata from MCP server (RFC 9728 + RFC 8414)
- Dynamic client registration (RFC 7591)
- PKCE flow (RFC 7636) with S256 code challenge
- Refresh token handling with 5-minute expiry buffer
- DPoP support mentioned in AGENTS.md
- State and verifier storage in `pending_oauth_state` and `pending_pkce_verifier`

### Credential Provider Support
✓ Already fully implemented
- Link to existing credential_provider records
- Support for api_key, bearer, basic, oauth2 auth methods
- Lazy-loaded accounts (ADR mentioned: "lazy-load accounts, de-emphasize advanced tabs")

### No Authentication
✓ Already fully implemented
- auth_mode defaults to "none"

